node.text:
Nothing feels better than AFTER a long distance run😅 
Took a ride to one of my fav place with a view and got a 3 mile run in. Running was always something really hard for me when I was younger and I HATED it but now it’s become a very important my mental health.

Walking/ jogging has always been incorporated during my weight loss journey and I’ve just kept it in my routine, it’s not always easy but the runners high is something else!! Plus it always makes me feel skinnier after 🤣

Wore a @get_tighterr belt to keep me feeling tight and less jiggly during my run. I wear a medium for my belt! Have you got yours yet?

node.text:
Sometimes I wonder if I had all the loose skin on my body removed, would I be completely happy with the way I look?

I’d like to think that but I’d probably find something else to be insecure about 😅
It’s sad because I know a lot of it has to do with social media and the way we compare ourselves. Body dysmorphia is SOOO real and I can’t wait for the day I can look at myself and be completely happy with the way I see myself. We are all so much more than that number on the scale, our clothing size, loose skin, etc.. as long as your healthy or working on it, that’s all that matters. Stay beautiful!! 🤟🏽✨

What was your wake up call?

Mine was the feeling of just being tired. Age 19 and I barely had energy to do anything! I felt uncomfortable in my clothes, uncomfortable in my body and just didn’t have the confidence I wanted to have. To this day, I still know that feeling and that’s enough to keep me motivated every single day 🙏🏽💪🏽

node.text:
There used to be days I dreamed of wearing clothes like this, but didn’t because I wasn’t comfortable with the way I looked, or couldn’t even find clothes like this because the women’s plus didn’t carry the style I wanted.
I went from a size 24 in jeans to a size 8-10 and a size 3x shirt to a small-medium. I remember trying on a size 14 jeans and I CRIED because I was so happy to be out of the plus size👏🏽
I deff gotta say, buying new clothes was probably one of the most motivating things during my weight loss. Keep a goal outfit for yourself and let it motivate you!💪🏽

Read this to yourself:

“I am talented and motivated, even when I get tired and frustrated i will be patient with myself. I am motivating and inspiring others with my strength and determination and I am so proud of the person I have become!”

There is absolutely NO reason to speak negative to yourself. Make your thoughts and words kind because you are your biggest supporter 🤟🏽

node.text:
2 years ago today, I was going in for surgery to get the last biopsy of my cancerous lymph node.

2 years ago, I got told I was cancer free after 6 months of chemo, many scans, a month of radiation and almost a whole year of playing the waiting game.

Today I am 2 years CANCER FREE and I couldn’t be anymore thankful, I am so truly blessed to be where I am at in life. Thank you to Jesus and all his glory for giving me many many miracles and keeping me strong through my crazy life💕🤟🏽🙏🏽
